dismissalText.commentary: Suraj Randiv c Doherty b Johnson 41 (50b 4x4 1x6 64m) SR: 82

dismissalComment.html: they have finally broken the partnership, it is Johnson again, five for him, Randiv goes for the big lofted shot down the ground off a full delivery, but mishits it high in the air and Doherty settles under it at long off and takes it cleanly

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga b Doherty 34 (28b 7x4 0x6 42m) SR: 121.42

dismissalComment.html: Doherty strikes, Tharanga went back as he saw a marginally shortish one, it turned in sharply and beat his attempted cut to hit off stump, he was looking really good, Doherty is pumped up

Australia are appealing for caught behind, it was a fullish and wide one slanted across Mahela who went for the drive, Haddin took it tumbling to his right, Australia are sure about it, umpire de Silva walks across towards square leg to check if it has carried, it has gone very low but right in to Haddin's gloves, and umpire de Silva sends Mahela back after checking with the third umpire, Johnson strikes in his first over

Johnson has got Sanga, huge wicket, it is the slower one, bowled full close to off for the drive, mighty useful on this track, Sanga comes forward and looks to push hard. but pops it straight to short extra cover
Johnson is pumped up, he has gone through Mendis' defenses with a pacy yorker from over the stumps that swung in a bit late to clatter in to off and middle

commentTextItems.html: Clarke does it in a  way characteristic of this innings and of his general approach to spin, down the track and caresses a flighted ball with the turn between mid on and midwicket

commentPostTextItems.html: That will be all from us for this game. Join us for the 2nd ODI on Sunday from Hambantota. This is Abhishek Purohit signing off. Thanks for all the feedback. Cheers!

Clarke: "The wicket was fantastic, it was dry but held together better than I expected. It is important that I lead from the front, it is great having Ponting at No 3 with all that experience at the other end."

Mitchell Johnson is the Man of the Match for his 6 for 31. Johnson: "I enjoyed myself, good to get that win on the board after the Twenty20 losses, Brett Lee getting his 350th ODI wicket was exciting as well. I enjoyed getting Sanga out, always exciting to get one of their top players out."
Dilshan: "This was not a 190 wicket, we did not bat well. Our shot selection was not good, it was a good toss to win, I think our spinners bowled well, but they did not have the runs to defend."

Three half-centuries in a chase of 192, Watson threatened to blow Sri Lanka away before falling to spin, Ajantha Mendis threatened to do an encore of the second T20 before Ponting and Clarke dug in to ensure Australia motored to victory. Australia will be tested by the Sri Lanka spinners, who were short in general today, in bigger chases but today Mitchell Johnson has set up a comprehensive win with his career-best haul

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga b Doherty 34 (28b 7x4 0x6 42m) SR: 121.42

dismissalComment.html: Doherty strikes, Tharanga went back as he saw a marginally shortish one, it turned in sharply and beat his attempted cut to hit off stump, he was looking really good, Doherty is pumped up

headshotImage.longCaption: David Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.longCaption: Doug Bollinger player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Tillakaratne Dilshan c Bollinger b DJ Hussey 29 (41b 4x4 0x6 55m) SR: 70.73

dismissalComment.html: Dilshan has thrown it away, he was looking increasingly impatient, got down the track as he saw some flight outside off, but was still not close enough to the ball as he blasted it straight to mid off

dismissalText.commentary: Mahela Jayawardene c †Haddin b Johnson 3 (8b 0x4 0x6 10m) SR: 37.5

dismissalComment.html: Australia are appealing for caught behind, it was a fullish and wide one slanted across Mahela who went for the drive, Haddin took it tumbling to his right, Australia are sure about it, umpire de Silva walks across towards square leg to check if it has carried, it has gone very low but right in to Haddin's gloves, and umpire de Silva sends Mahela back after checking with the third umpire, Johnson strikes in his first over

dismissalText.commentary: Kumar Sangakkara c Smith b Johnson 16 (19b 3x4 0x6 36m) SR: 84.21

dismissalComment.html: Johnson has got Sanga, huge wicket, it is the slower one, bowled full close to off for the drive, mighty useful on this track, Sanga comes forward and looks to push hard. but pops it straight to short extra cover

headshotImage.longCaption: Doug Bollinger player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Dinesh Chandimal c Clarke b Bollinger 12 (13b 1x4 0x6 21m) SR: 92.3

dismissalComment.html: what a catch that is from Michael Clarke, Doug slanted a length ball across Chandimal who got too far across and had a poke at it, the edge went between Haddin and Clarke at wide slip who flew to his left and grabbed the ball one-handed at it almost rushed passed him, superb reflexes from the captain, Australia on top

dismissalText.commentary: Jeevan Mendis b Johnson 2 (6b 0x4 0x6 8m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: Johnson is pumped up, he has gone through Mendis' defenses with a pacy yorker from over the stumps that swung in a bit late to clatter in to off and middle

dismissalText.commentary: Angelo Mathews c Watson b Johnson 15 (18b 3x4 0x6 31m) SR: 83.33

dismissalComment.html: Angelo becomes the latest Sri Lanka batsman to throw it away, these shots are certainly not on on this pitch, he looks to come down the track and make room to clobber a pitched up delivery over mid off, but cannot clear the man, straight to him

dismissalText.commentary: Suraj Randiv c Doherty b Johnson 41 (50b 4x4 1x6 64m) SR: 82

dismissalComment.html: they have finally broken the partnership, it is Johnson again, five for him, Randiv goes for the big lofted shot down the ground off a full delivery, but mishits it high in the air and Doherty settles under it at long off and takes it cleanly

dismissalText.commentary: Ajantha Mendis b Johnson 0 (5b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: and gets his sixth with a slanted length ball that hits the top of off stump, Mendis just went pushing away from his body and was nowhere near the line of the ball

headshotImage.longCaption: Michael Hussey player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Nuwan Kulasekara c MEK Hussey b Lee 34 (57b 2x4 2x6 79m) SR: 59.64

dismissalComment.html: superb shot, but what a catch from Mike Hussey, Lee gets his 350th ODI wicket, banged it in short and Nuwan cracked the pull right out of the middle of the bat, it was dying in front of Hussey at deep midwicket, but he dived forward to take the ball close to the ground

headshotImage.caption: Suraj Randiv player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Suraj Randiv player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shane Watson c Jayawardene b Randiv 69 (51b 5x4 6x6 49m) SR: 135.29

dismissalComment.html: Watson has fallen, the method was bound to come undone at least off one delivery, happened this time, Randiv tossed it up around middle and leg, Watson lunged for the sweep, and got a top edge that swirled to the man at short fine leg who went a few steps back and to his left to take the ball as it came over his shoulder

headshotImage.caption: Ajantha Mendis player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ajantha Mendis player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Brad Haddin b BAW Mendis 12 (18b 1x4 0x6 36m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: Haddin can't survive this over, he hasn't looked comfortable at all, tosses it up, it is the one that breaks back in, Haddin just plays all around it, probably for the one turning away, and middle stump is pegged back
